Experiment 6: Create Simple Calculations in Excel

1. Direct Cell Formula:

In cell A1, type 100. In cell B1, type 50.

In cell C1, type:
=A1-B1
(It will display 50.)



2. Using Defined Names:

Click on cell A1, then click in the Name Box (left of the formula bar) and type Revenue.

Click on cell B1, then define it as Expenses.

In cell C2, type:
=Revenue-Expenses



3. Creating Formulas with the Function Wizard:

Click on Formulas > Insert Function.

Select a function (for example, SUM) and follow the wizard to choose the cell range.
